@NODE "Convert"

       @{b}Silent@{ub}         - Silent mode ON/OFF
                        If its ON, the MP3 will be played during conversion.

       @{b}Source@{ub}         - The MP3 that is to be converted!

       @{b}Destination@{ub}    - The location of the Output WAVE file...

       @{b}Begin!@{ub}         - Begin Conversion :)..

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Preferences"

       @{b}Output Quality@{ub} - The Output quality! :) (LOW/MED/HIGH)
                        If you sett it thru the icon, use 0,1,2
                        2 is the highest quality..
                        Tooltype=SOUNDQUALITY

       @{b}Frequency div.@{ub} - Frequency division.. (1X/2X/4X)
                        If you set it thru the icon ... use 0,1,2..
                        0 is the highest quality..
                        Tooltype=FREQUENCYDIV

       @{b}Repeat@{ub}         - Repeat the song.. (ON/OFF)
                        If you set it thru the icon use 0 or 1 ..
                        0=OFF  ..  1=ON ..
                        Tooltype=REPEAT

       @{b}Volume@{ub}         - This is the volume slider.. A LOW setting on
                        it is recommended, to avoid disturbance..
                        (Use the volume on your stereo instead)
                        If you set it thru the ICON a value between
                        0-250 is used .. Use X*10!.. ex. 10.. 20.. 30...etc.
                        Tooltype=VOLUME

       @{b}Mode@{ub}           - Here you specify if you want MONO/STEREO...
                        0=MONO .. 1=STEREO..
                        Tooltype=MODE

       @{b}Priority@{ub}       - Here tyou specify the PRIORITY the program is
                        supposed to run in .. (Mpega)..
                        This is a value between -128>128...
                        Tooltype=PRI

       @{b}Paths@{ub}          - Location of Paths..
                        @{b}MpegA@{ub} - Location of the MpegA (main exe)
                        @{u}Use of a ASSIGN is @{b}@{u}INDEED!@{uu}@{ub} recomeded!!..
                        (otherwise it may have problems working.)
                        Tooltype=PROGLOCATION

                        @{b}Mp3s@{ub}  - Path where all the MPs are located!
                        Also here i @{b}@{u}RECOMMEND@{uu}@{ub} that you put the PATH
                        to a @{b}ASSIGN@{ub} or else.. U MAY experience probs .. :/
                        Tooltype=SLOCATION

                        From version 0.7 the the @{b}PATHS@{ub} are saved automaticly! :)
                        @{u}This kills some bugs@{uu} ..

       @{b}Mixing Freq@{ub}    - This sets the current mixing frequency....
                        For example, if you are runing on a PAL screen a sensible value
                        would be 28.... (kHz)... In ChaoZgui u just enter the Khz value!
                        You can also turn mixing frequency ON/OFF with the button to the
                        right of the gadget..
                        0=OFF .. 1=ON
                        Tooltype=MIXINGFREQ  <- For the Mixing Freq
                        Tooltype=MIXING      <- To make it ON/OFF...

       @{b}Audio Buffer@{ub}   - This is the audio buffer, each "snap" in the gadget
                        is ONE second... A good value of the Buffer is around 5-10...
                        Tooltype=ABUFFER    (10000=1s)

       @{b}Buffer@{ub}         - This is the buffer, here you determine how many KB
                        mpega should read in each time....
                        Tootype=IBUFFER

@ENDNODE

